Class AccessVerifyConnectionSpec

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.med.vistalink.adapter.cci.VistaLinkConnectionSpecImpl
      • gov.va.med.srcalc.vista.vistalink.AccessVerifyConnectionSpec
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    gov.va.med.vistalink.adapter.cci.VistaLinkConnectionSpec, javax.resource.cci.ConnectionSpec

    public final class AccessVerifyConnectionSpec
extends gov.va.med.vistalink.adapter.cci.VistaLinkConnectionSpecImpl

    A VistaLinkConnectionSpec for access/verify-code re-authentication. Immutable except for the division attribute.

    Based on KaajeeVistaLinkConnectionSpec provided by KAAJEE. (Why doesn't VistALink provide this out of the box?)

                          java.lang.String accessCode,
                          java.lang.String verifyCode,
                          java.lang.String clientIp)
        Constructs an instance with the given properties.
        Parameters:
        division - station # (external format) of the division to log the user in against
        accessCode - user access code. Must not be null.
        verifyCode - user verify code. Must not be null.
        clientIp - the client's IP address for signon logging. Must not be null.
